Kenuon Windrunner<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umicewandu02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Micewandu02</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 5:02:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me out with new legs =)</span><hr size=1> Um, Kromrif Military Legs ??  Not as good as gladiator chain, but these legs are way better than verm, ES . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminasplainrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MinasPlainrunner </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 7:56:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me out with new legs =)</span><hr size=1> Any idea what faction the guy who drops them is on? A name would help to so I could check. Also, I am unable to to the Kromiff military leggings quest, for it requires good dorf faction. <p><html>
<center>
Minas Plainrunner, lvl 5<b>4</b> Member of the Harbingers (HarBLINGers), Karana.</center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquigsby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quigsby</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 10:54:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me out with new legs =)</span><hr size=1> Well, you could always have a newbie of yours do it, or a friend. ;)  I did the Coldain Military Wristgaurd with my lvl 6 troll warrior who worships Rallos Zek.  Had a group intercept the dorf, and I looted the bracer.  Easy. <p><font color="#006600"><font size=+2>Quigsby Quickfoot</font></font>
<br><font color="#FF0000"><font size=+1>59th Preserver of Zebuxoruk</font></font>
<br><a href="http://www.requiemofsouls.com"><font color="663399"><font size=+1>Requiem of Souls</font></font></a><br>
"Thought this be madness, yet there is method in't."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 9:07:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me out with new legs =)</span><hr size=1> Gladiator Chain Leggings drop off Bjrakor the Cold in the arena.<br>
Kromriff Military Leggings drop off Fergul Frostsky (the spawned quest version).<br>
<br>
You should be able to do the Kromriff military leggings quest fairly easily ... take a friend who's non KOS to coldain in to CC, kill orcs till you get the bottle of acid (or kill the queen for sceptre), have your friend loot the item and turn it in to Erdaf.  Then have your friend turn in the gem of persuasion to Vores ... you turn in the blood wolf harness ... bingo, you have the control harness and you can go on alone from there. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>56 Preserver, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 1:46:55 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me out with new legs =)</span><hr size=1> Hey Minas, a few thoughts.<br>
<br>
Crystal Chitin Leggings - (Edit Item)<br>
Races: ALL - Classes: BRD CLR DRU PAL RNG SHD SHM WAR (LORE - MAGIC)<br>
Stats: AC: 9 - Wt: 4 - Slot: legs<br>
Attributes: STA+5 MANA+25 <br>
Average Price: 5,000 <br>
<br>
Not great stats, but the look is incredible.  I've seen a few people running around on our server with these and the look is better, and the stats are still better than gnome skin.  eqdruids has it's item ranking one step lower than the gatorscale legs.  Pretty much anything else isn't as good as the gatorscale or is no drop.<br>
<br>
Things that are better that are no drop in decreasing point order:<br>
Nature Walker's Greaves (ToV but could be a while)<br>
Silver Chains**  (ToV, no drop)  <br>
Elder Spiritist's Greaves (Trak but could be a while)<br>
Gladiator's Chain Leggings  (Giants in Kael, wrong faction for these, no drop)<br>
Ancient Wurm Hide Greaves  (ToV, no drop)<br>
Kromrif Military Leggings  (Giant in GD, wrong faction for these, no drop)<br>
Flayed Paebala Leggings  (DN, no drop, off of Paebala's not chitari)<br>
Oiled Greaves  (Skyshrine worth about 30K, monks usualy get first)<br>
Vermiculated Greaves  (Fear, no drop)<br>
Withered Leather Leggings (Drops in Hole, about 1K)<br>
<br>
Most the the stuff is either no drop, very expensive, or on the wrong faction for us.   You're probably best off sticking with the gnome if you got enough wiz with it or use the gatorscale if not.  If I rember right you were at 200 wis with the legs and the brawl stick so either go with High ac on the legs or resists.<br>
<br>
Of the no drop items, I'm figureing the vermi will roll around eventualy and most everyone above you has either vermi or ES legs. ;)  Oh, and there is allways the chance that the next time we are at hate2, the harmony legs might drop as well. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Preserver of the 55th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR>
